# HARD DELETED: entire `components/` directory

```txt
C:\JackProject\afenda-vercel\components   ← GONE. THE WHOLE TREE.
```

The operator **hard-deleted the entire repo-root `components/` folder** — not a subfolder, not “mostly migrated,” **the full directory**.

**Recreating `components/` or any path under it is a VIOLATION** for every agent, IDE, merge tool, generator, and human — no exceptions, no “just ui,” no “just one file,” no “temporary until build passes.”

---

## The one sentence rule

```txt
components/ MUST NOT EXIST ON DISK. Fix imports forward into components2/ (and feature modules). Never mkdir components.
```

---

## Forbidden (all VIOLATIONS)

| Action | Status |
|---|---|
| `mkdir components` or restoring `components/` from git / another branch | **VIOLATION** |
| Re-adding `components/ui/**`, `components/workbench/**`, `components/nexus/**`, `components/auth/**`, … | **VIOLATION** |
| `shadcn add` or CLI output targeting `components/` | **VIOLATION** — redirect output to `components2/ui/` |
| “I'll only restore `components/ui` for the build” | **VIOLATION** |
| Copying one deleted file back “to unblock typecheck” | **VIOLATION** |
| Keeping `#components/*` imports while recreating the folder | **VIOLATION** — change imports, do not recreate the tree |

---

## Canonical homes (fix forward)

| Was under deleted `components/` | Use instead |
|---|---|
| Shell / workbench chrome | `components2/app-shell/**` · `#app-shell` · `#app-shell/client` |
| UI primitives (shadcn shelf) | `components2/ui/**` · `#components2/ui/*` |
| Portal chrome | `components2/portal-shell/**` |
| Metadata renderers | `components2/metadata/**` · `#components2/metadata` |
| Marketing / dev overlays | `components2/marketing/**` · `components2/dev/**` |
| ERP feature UI | `lib/features/<module>/components/**` |
| Ask-docs Lynx / feedback (if still needed) | `components2/**` or `lib/ask-docs/**` — **not** `components/` |

**Do not consult old docs that say `components/ui` or `#components/ui/*` as current — that path is retired with the deleted directory.**

---

## Required behavior before creating ANY path

1. If the path starts with `components/` → **stop**. You are violating this rule.
2. Broken `#components/...` import → **retarget** to `components2/` or the feature module; **never** recreate `components/` to satisfy the alias.
3. User asks to “bring back components” → **refuse by default**; only a deliberate **`git revert` of the deletion commit** is allowed, not hand-written re-creation.
4. Merge conflict: one side deleted `components/` → **keep deleted**; fix callers in the winning migration.

---

## Mechanical enforcement

`scripts/check-agent-contract.mjs` **fails CI** if `components/` exists at repo root.

Treat any PR that adds `components/` as **block merge** — delete the directory again, fix imports forward, run ESLint on touched paths + `pnpm typecheck`.

